_with_philadelp.html }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"murder rate\">{{cite web|url=http://www.myfoxdc.com/dpp/news/local/dc-murder-rate-lowest-in-45-years-122809|title=DC Murder Rate Lowest in 45 Years|author=Paul Wagner|date=December 28, 2009|publisher=myfoxdc}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"new cropp\">{{cite web |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/08/21/AR2006082101598.html |title=New Cropp Fliers Attack Fenty |accessdate=2007-05-19 |last=Silverman |first=Elissa |author2=Lori Montgomery |date=August 22, 2006 |work=The Washington Post |page= B02 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"new mayor\">{{cite web|last=Libby|first=Lewis|url=https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=6479556|title=The Nation's Capital Gets a New Mayor|publisher=[[National Public Radio]]|date=November 13, 2006|accessdate=16 October 2016}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"oberlin\">{{cite news |title=Fenty to teach at Oberlin in the fall |first=Nikita |last=Stewart |work=The Washington Post |date=January 19, 2011 |url=http://voices.washingtonpost.com/dc/2011/01/fenty_to_teach_at_oberlin_in_t.html }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"on DC politics\">[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OkOKJxq7aiY Q&A Cafe: Adrian Fenty on DC Politics part 2]. YouTube (December 16, 2007). Retrieved on 2010-11-13.</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"oust\">{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2007/06/11/AR2007061102383.html|title=Fenty To Oust Janey Today|author=David Nakamura|date=June 12, 2007|work=Washington Post}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"psat\">[http://www.collegeboard.com/student/testing/psat/about.html PSAT/NMSQT \u2013 The Preliminary SAT/National Merit Scholarship Qualifying Test]. Collegeboard.com. Retrieved on 2010-11-13.</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"public schools\">{{cite news|url=|title=Fenty takes control of public schools|last=Emerling|first=Gary|date=June 13, 2007|publisher=[[The Washington Times]]}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"pledges support\">{{cite news |title=Fenty pledges support for Gray, says he won't run fo