hingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/07/22/AR2006072200632.html |title=Fenty Emerges From D.C. Pack |accessdate=2007-05-19 |last=Barnes |first=Robert |author2=Lori Montgomery |date=July 23, 2006 |work=The Washington Post |page= A01 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"fitness\">{{cite news|author= David Nakamura|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/05/29/AR2008052903894_2.html |title=Fenty's Fitness for Office|date=May 30, 2008 |work=The Washington Post|quote=At 6 feet & 180 pounds, Fenty appears the picture of fit, but he hasn't always been that way. In 2000 ... Fenty did not run a single time. He also reached about 215 pounds ...}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"fleet feet\">The store is now co-owned by Adrian's brother Sean and Sean's wife.{{cite web|url=http://www.fleetfeetdc.com/content/view/41/69/|title= Fleet Feet D.C. About Us|accessdate=August 25, 2011}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"fleet feet 2\">{{cite web|url=http://fleetfeetdc.com/anniversary.html|title= FLEET FEET WASHINGTON, D.C. HISTORY|accessdate=April 1, 2017}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"gray leads\">[http://www.washingtoncitypaper.com/blogs/looselips/2010/09/08/sneak-preview-of-city-paperkojo-nnamdi-show-poll/ Vincent Gray Leads Adrian Fenty in City Paper/Kojo Nnamdi Show Poll]</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Jaffee 11-2008\">{{cite web |url=http://www.washingtonian.com/print/articles/6/173/9958.html |title=Adrian Fenty: Born to Run |accessdate=2009-02-05 |last=Jaffe |first=Harry |date=November 2008 |publisher=[[Washingtonian (magazine)|The Washingtonian]] }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"jarvis ousted\">{{cite news |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-545904.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110516161723/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-545904.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=May 16, 2011 |title= Council Member Jarvis Ousted in D.C. Primary; Fenty Defeats Veteran Lawmaker |accessdate=2007-05-19 |last=Chan |first=Sewell |date=September 13, 2000 |work=The Washington Post }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"joins D.C.\