a, Myanmar Sign Military Cooperation Agreement|url=http://www.defenseworld.net/news/16368/Russia__Myanmar_Sign_Military_Cooperation_Agreement#.WhzGr0y-Ihs|website=www.defenseworld.net|accessdate=29 November 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Collapsible list\n| title = Former:\n| {{flag|Union of Burma}} (1948\u20131962)\n* [[Anti-Fascist People's Freedom League|AFPFL]]\n| {{flagdeco|Myanmar|1974}} [[Military junta|Military governments]] (1962\u20132011)\n* [[Burmese Way to Socialism|Socialist Republic of the Union of Burma]] (1962\u20131988)\n* [[State Peace and Development Council|Union of Myanmar]] (1988\u20132011)\n| '''Formerly supported by:'''\n| {{flag|Yugoslavia}} (1952\u20131988)<ref>Vojni leksikon [Military Lexicon] (Beograd: Vojnoizdavacki zavod, 1981), p. 71.</ref><ref>Bertil Lintner, Burma in Revolt: Opium and Insurgency since 1948, p. 154.</ref><ref>NARA, RG 59, 690B.9321/12-2253, Memorandum of Conversation between General Ne Win and the Army and Air Attach\u00e9s of the U.S. Embassy in Burma, 22 December 1953.</ref><ref>\u010cavo\u0161ki, Jovan. Arming Nonalignment: Yugoslavia's Relations with Burma and the Cold War in Asia (1950\u20131955). Washington, D.C.: Cold War International History Project, Woodrow Wilson International Center for Scholars, 2010. Print.</ref>\n}}\n----\n'''Allied groups:'''<br />{{flagicon image|United Wa State Party flag2.png}} [[United Wa State Party|UWSP]]/[[United Wa State Army|UWSA]]\n{{Collapsible list\n| title = Former:\n| {{flagicon image|Karenni National People's Liberation Front flag.png}} [[Karenni National People's Liberation Front|KNPLF]] (1978\u20132009)\n| [[New Democratic Army - Kachin|NDA-K]] (1989\u20132009)\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of DKBA.png}} [[Democratic Karen Buddhist Army|DKBA]] (1994\u20132010)\n}}\n| combatant2  = '''[[Northern Alliance (Myanmar)|Northern Alliance]]'''\n* {{flagicon image|Infobox AA.png}} [[Arakan Army (Kachin State)|ULA/AA]]\n* {{flagicon image|Kachin Independence Army flag.svg}} [[Kachin Independen