ag of Jihad.svg}} [[Mujahideen#Myanmar (Burma)|Mujahideen]] (1948\u20131961)\n| {{flagicon image|Pa-o nationality flag.png}} [[Pa-O National Army|PNA]] (1949\u20131991)\n| {{flagdeco|Taiwan|army}} [[Kuomintang in Burma|KMT]] (1950\u20131961)<ref name=\"Gibson\">{{cite book|title=The Secret Army: Chiang Kai-shek and the Drug Warlords of the Golden Triangle|publisher=John Wiley and Sons|author=Richard Michael Gibson|year=2011|pages=85\u201390|isbn=978-0-470-83018-5}}</ref>\n| {{flagicon image|Shan State Army flag.png}} [[Shan State Army|SSA]] (1964\u20131976)\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of the Wa National Army.svg}} [[Wa National Army|WNA]] (1974\u20131997)\n| {{flagicon image|Mong Tai Army flag.svg}} [[Mong Tai Army|MTA]] (1985\u20131996)\n| {{flagicon image|Shan State National Army.svg}} [[Shan State National Army|SSNA]] (1995\u20132005)\n| [[God's Army (revolutionary group)|God's Army]] (1997\u20132006)\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of the VBSW.png}} [[Vigorous Burmese Student Warriors|VBSW]] (1999\u20132013)\n| '''''[[List of insurgent groups in Myanmar#Defunct insurgent groups|...and others]]'''''\n| '''Formerly supported by:'''\n| {{flag|Thailand}} (1948\u20131995)<ref name=\"Lintner1995\">{{cite news|last1=Lintner|first1=Bertil|title=Recent Developments on Thai-Myanmar Border. IBRU Boundary and Security Bulletin|page=72}}</ref><ref name=\"Thai\"/>\n| {{flag|Pakistan}} (1948\u20131950){{efn|Support to the mujahideen only.<ref name=\"UNu\"/>}}\n| {{flag|Taiwan}} (1950\u20131980s){{efn|Support to the Kuomintang and the Wa National Army only.<ref name=\"Gibson\"/>}}\n| {{flag|United States}} (1951\u20131953){{efn|Support to the Kuomintang only.<ref name=\"Gibson\"/>}}\n| {{flag|China}} (1968\u20131988){{efn|Alleged support to the Communist Party of Burma from 1968 to 1988.<ref name=\"Gibson\"/>}}\n}}\n| commander1  = {{plainlist|\n* {{flagdeco|Myanmar}} [[Aung San Suu Kyi]]\n* {{flagdeco|Myanmar}} [[Win Myint (politician, born 1951)|Win Myint]]\n* {{flagdeco|Myanmar|army}}